FIGURE 22.1 Blood collection tube set for cetacean blood. The orange-topped tube is a serum separator tube and contains thrombin to induce clotting. The pale blue-topped tube contains 3.2% sodium citrate and is useful for coagulation assays and determination of plasma fibrinogen concentrations. The lavender-topped tube contains potassium EDTA and is useful for hematology and sedimentation rate determinations. 